data.value:
The equation PV = nRT describes the properties of an ideal gas inside a container.
Pressure (P) is measured in atmospheres (atm), Volume (V) is measured in liters (L), Number of gas molecules (n) is measured in moles (mol), R is the ideal gas constant, and Temperatue (T) is measured in Kelvin (K).
